## 2. Use

No individual or legal entity is authorized to:

* copy the project in whole or in part;
* modify the code;
* create derivative versions;
* distribute copies;
* publish forks;
* redistribute the documentation;
* reuse FUT-K algorithms or implementations in other projects;
* train derivative models using assets exclusive to the project;
* reproduce the system architecture, in whole or in part, for distribution.

Any use depends on the author's prior and express authorization.

### 2.1 Permitted evaluation use

As the sole exceptions to Section 2, the author grants a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, revocable permission to:

* clone this repository and run FUT-K locally for personal, non-commercial
  evaluation, study and testing, including reproducing the published
  validation results;
* create a fork on the hosting platform solely to prepare and submit a
  contribution to the official repository under the CLA (`CLA.md`).

This permission grants no other right listed in Section 2, no right under
Section 3 (Commercial Use), and may be revoked by the author at any time.

